<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-208-210  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 208 210.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  March 7 1990 v139 pC7(N) pD6(L) 23 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A new transmission for the 90's? (automobiletransmissions)(Business Technology)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fisher, Lawrence M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Porsche AG will include a new automatic transmission on its carsin the US, in the spring or summer of 1990, which will include amicroprocessor that considers 40 kinds of data in makingdecisions.andP;  A Porsche representative says the new transmission,called Tiptronic, operates like other automatic transmissions, butit is smarter.andP;  A microprocessor receives data from electronicsensors that measure lateral forces in a turn as well as forwardacceleration, engine and air temperature, and even a driver'sdriving style.andP;  The microprocessor then chooses from between fiveshifting patterns.andP;  This sort of a transmission could become apopular device in the future, as automobiles are forced to meettougher emission and efficiency requirements.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Porsche AG (product development).andO;Topic:     AutomobilesAutomobile IndustryProduct DevelopmentMicroprocessors.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   A smarter automatic transmission. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>